OL,3,CA divide in power: How Grenfell
OL,4,Cexposed Britain's social housing crisis
OL,6,FWho bothered to ensure those who
OL,7,Fsurvived were treated with dignity in
OL,8,Fproper housing.
OL,10,FThose who died, those who survived,
OL,11,Fwere overwhelmingly working-class,
OL,12,Foverwhelmingly from ethnic minority
OL,13,Fbackgrounds. Lawyers for the survivors
OL,14,Fcalled race the "elephant in the room".
OL,16,FSeven years. Do we live in a post-
OL,17,FGrenfell Britain? Was it a moment
OL,18,Fwhere everything changed? Was it a
OL,19,Fturning point?
